default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSexual Violencedefault: 
defaultThe risk of depression and anxiety
default is three to four times higher for those who have experienced 
defaultgender-based violence
default, and around a third of all survivors of 
defaultrape experience 
defaultPosttraumatic Stress Disorder
default.
default  Sexual violence can result in acute and chronic physical disabilities, for example 
defaultsevere pain during menstruation 
defaultor prolonged menstrual bleeding, as well as long term 
defaultgenital-anal trauma
default and
default sexually trans
defaultmitted infections
