default6.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEnsure cdefaulthildren with disabilities defaulthave access defaultto defaulta defaultquality defaulteducation. defaultA quality education is one that is grounded in respect for human rights and gender equity, that is accessible to all children without discrimination, and one in which all children are encouraged to fulfil their 
defaultcapabilities.  It includes a learning environ
defaultment that is learner-friendly, safe and healthy for all children with mechanisms to prevent and respond to violence.  A quality education is accountable to children through the participation of children, families and communities in school governance and de
defaultcision –making. 
