defaultPlan maintains a database of its 1.4 million sponsored children. The dataset used for the report spans 30 countries and asks 
defaultcomparable questions across each of them, giving a powerful and comprehensive source of data for research. Note though that children are selected for sponsorship in various ways, not as a proportionate representation of the wider child population. The data
default of the research therefore cannot be extrapolated to national populations but does give a solid insight into the different experiences of children with and without disabilities and highlights important areas for future research.
